      <biogHist id="md5-6c8fee36ed8700323c1b4ffd2cea9303">
        <p>The Academy was founded in 1902 as the North Alberta Medical Association. After successive name changes (Central Alberta Medical Association, 1909-1912; Edmonton Medical Society, 1912- 1914) it was incorporated under its present title in 1920.  Its purpose has remained unchanged:  to advance the science of medicine, medical education, public health and the medical profession and to provide unity within the profession, particularly in Edmonton.</p>
      </biogHist>
